.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::GiftWrap \- NIP\-59 gift wrap encryption
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&    use Net::Nostr::GiftWrap;
\&    use Net::Nostr::Key;
\&
\&    my $sender    = Net::Nostr::Key\->new;
\&    my $recipient = Net::Nostr::Key\->new;
\&
\&    # Create an unsigned rumor
\&    my $rumor = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->create_rumor(
\&        pubkey  => $sender\->pubkey_hex,
\&        kind    => 1,
\&        content => \*(AqAre you going to the party tonight?\*(Aq,
\&        tags    => [],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Seal and wrap in one step
\&    my $wrap = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->seal_and_wrap(
\&        rumor            => $rumor,
\&        sender_key       => $sender,
\&        recipient_pubkey => $recipient\->pubkey_hex,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Recipient unwraps
\&    my ($unwrapped, $sender_pubkey) = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->unwrap(
\&        event         => $wrap,
\&        recipient_key => $recipient,
\&    );
\&    say $unwrapped\->content;  # "Are you going to the party tonight?"
\&    say $sender_pubkey;       # sender\*(Aqs pubkey (from seal)
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-59 gift wrapping, a protocol for encapsulating any Nostr
event to obscure metadata. Uses three layers:
.IP "\fBRumor\fR \- An unsigned event. Provides deniability if leaked." 4
.IX Item "Rumor - An unsigned event. Provides deniability if leaked."
.PD 0
.IP "\fBSeal\fR (kind 13) \- Encrypts the rumor with the sender\*(Aqs key. Identifies the author without revealing content or recipient. Tags are always empty." 4
.IX Item "Seal (kind 13) - Encrypts the rumor with the sender's key. Identifies the author without revealing content or recipient. Tags are always empty."
.ie n .IP "\fBGift wrap\fR (kind 1059) \- Encrypts the seal with a random one\-time key. Includes a ""p"" tag for routing to the recipient." 4
.el .IP "\fBGift wrap\fR (kind 1059) \- Encrypts the seal with a random one\-time key. Includes a \f(CWp\fR tag for routing to the recipient." 4
.IX Item "Gift wrap (kind 1059) - Encrypts the seal with a random one-time key. Includes a p tag for routing to the recipient."
.PD
.PP
Encryption uses NIP\-44. Timestamps on seals and
gift wraps are randomized up to two days in the past to thwart time\-analysis
attacks.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS create_rumor
.IX Subsection "create_rumor"
.Vb 6
\&    my $rumor = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->create_rumor(
\&        pubkey  => $pubkey_hex,
\&        kind    => 14,
\&        content => \*(AqHello!\*(Aq,
\&        tags    => [[\*(Aqp\*(Aq, $recipient_pubkey]],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates an unsigned event (rumor). Arguments are passed to
\&\f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Event\->new\*(C'\fR and the signature is removed.
.SS seal
.IX Subsection "seal"
.Vb 5
\&    my $seal = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->seal(
\&        rumor            => $rumor,
\&        sender_key       => $sender,
\&        recipient_pubkey => $recipient\->pubkey_hex,
\&    );
\&
\&    say $seal\->kind;                   # 13
\&    say $seal\->pubkey eq $sender\->pubkey_hex;  # 1 (signed by sender)
\&    say scalar @{$seal\->tags};         # 0 (always empty)
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 13 seal event. The rumor is JSON\-encoded and encrypted
with NIP\-44 using the sender\*(Aqs private key and recipient\*(Aqs public key.
The seal is signed by the sender. Tags are empty per the spec (except
when \f(CW\*(C`expiration\*(C'\fR is explicitly requested, per NIP\-17).
.PP
Optional arguments: \f(CW\*(C`created_at\*(C'\fR (override random timestamp),
\&\f(CW\*(C`expiration\*(C'\fR (add expiration tag for disappearing messages).
.SS wrap
.IX Subsection "wrap"
.Vb 4
\&    my $wrap = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->wrap(
\&        seal             => $seal,
\&        recipient_pubkey => $recipient\->pubkey_hex,
\&    );
\&
\&    say $wrap\->kind;    # 1059
\&    say $wrap\->pubkey;  # random one\-time\-use pubkey (not the sender)
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 1059 gift wrap event. The seal is JSON\-encoded and encrypted
with NIP\-44 using a random one\-time key. A \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag is added for the
recipient.
.PP
Optional arguments: \f(CW\*(C`wrapper_key\*(C'\fR (override random key, for testing),
\&\f(CW\*(C`created_at\*(C'\fR (override random timestamp), \f(CW\*(C`expiration\*(C'\fR (add expiration
tag).
.SS seal_and_wrap
.IX Subsection "seal_and_wrap"
.Vb 5
\&    my $wrap = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->seal_and_wrap(
\&        rumor            => $rumor,
\&        sender_key       => $sender,
\&        recipient_pubkey => $recipient\->pubkey_hex,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Convenience method that calls "seal" then "wrap".
.PP
Optional arguments: \f(CW\*(C`expiration\*(C'\fR (gift wrap expiration),
\&\f(CW\*(C`seal_expiration\*(C'\fR (seal expiration).
.PP
Expiration example (disappearing messages):
.PP
.Vb 7
\&    my $wrap = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->seal_and_wrap(
\&        rumor            => $rumor,
\&        sender_key       => $sender,
\&        recipient_pubkey => $recipient\->pubkey_hex,
\&        expiration       => time() + 86400,
\&        seal_expiration  => time() + 86400,
\&    );
.Ve
.SS unwrap
.IX Subsection "unwrap"
.Vb 4
\&    my ($unwrapped, $sender_pubkey) = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->unwrap(
\&        event         => $gift_wrap_event,
\&        recipient_key => $recipient,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Decrypts a kind 1059 gift wrap event. Returns the rumor (unsigned event)
and the sender\*(Aqs public key (from the seal). The caller should verify
that \f(CW$sender_pubkey\fR matches \f(CW\*(C`$unwrapped\->pubkey\*(C'\fR for authentication
("receive" in Net::Nostr::DirectMessage does this automatically).
.PP
Croaks if the event is not kind 1059 or the seal is not kind 13.
.PP
\&\fBTrust boundary\fR: This method only decrypts and parses the layered
structure. It checks kind numbers but does \fBnot\fR verify the gift wrap
event\*(Aqs signature, event ID hash, or the seal event\*(Aqs signature. The
returned rumor is unsigned by design (for deniability). Callers receiving
gift wraps from untrusted sources should verify the outer event\*(Aqs
signature before calling \f(CW\*(C`unwrap\*(C'\fR.
.SS "Multi\-recipient wrapping"
.IX Subsection "Multi-recipient wrapping"
A single rumor can be wrapped individually for each recipient:
.PP
.Vb 8
\&    for my $pubkey (@recipient_pubkeys) {
\&        my $wrap = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->seal_and_wrap(
\&            rumor            => $rumor,
\&            sender_key       => $sender,
\&            recipient_pubkey => $pubkey,
\&        );
\&        # publish $wrap to $pubkey\*(Aqs relays
\&    }
.Ve
.PP
The author can also retain an encrypted copy by wrapping to their own
pubkey:
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    my $self_copy = Net::Nostr::GiftWrap\->seal_and_wrap(
\&        rumor            => $rumor,
\&        sender_key       => $sender,
\&        recipient_pubkey => $sender\->pubkey_hex,
\&    );
.Ve
